SIMPLE: pavement
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pavement
<hw>Pave"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. LL.
<ets>pavamentum</ets>, L. <ets>pavimentum</ets>. See
<er>Pave</er>.]</ety> <def>That with which anything is paved; a floor or
covering of solid material, laid so as to make a hard and convenient
surface for travel; a paved road or sidewalk; a decorative interior
floor of tiles or colored bricks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The riches of heaven's <qex>pavement</qex>, trodden gold.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Pavement teeth</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>,
<cd>flattened teeth which in certain fishes, as the skates and
cestracionts, are arranged side by side, like tiles in a
pavement.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pavement</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pavement
<hw>Pave"ment</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To furnish with a pavement; to
pave.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧How richly
<xex>pavemented</xex>!⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paven</ent>⟦br⟧
